[b]Wolfe Wave Scanner Pro[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Searches a depth window of confirmed swings for every distinct, non-overlapping 5-point Wolfe Wave wedge — a contracting, alternating channel where point 5 tests the 1-3 trendline — not just the single highest-scoring one. Each candidate is scored 0-100 across eight structural criteria; every valid pattern draws its own wedge and EPA (Estimated Price at Arrival) target, tracked independently until price confirms or invalidates it.

Wolfe Waves are strongly interpretation-dependent — treat this as a structural setup finder with a quality score, not a signal machine: a found pattern means "a Wolfe-shaped geometry exists here, worth checking against context," not "enter now."

[b]Scoring[/b]
[list]
[*]Wedge structure (point 3 undercuts/exceeds point 1, point 5 extends beyond point 3)
[*]Channel contraction (real narrowing ratio + monotonic through the midpoint) and boundary slope consistency
[*]Point-4 channel containment
[*]Apex convergence of lines 1-3 and 2-4 ahead of point 5
[*]Point-5 trendline test against the 1-3 line
[*]Reward direction of point 5 vs. line 1-4, capped to a sane distance
[*]Timing and leg-time symmetry of the five legs
[/list]

[b]Features[/b]
[list]
[*]Best-of-window swing search across non-consecutive combinations, not just the last 5 swings
[*]Tracks multiple simultaneously valid, non-overlapping patterns at once — a second genuine Wolfe wave elsewhere on the chart isn't discarded just because it scores lower
[*]EPA target line from line 1-4 at the true 1-3/2-4 apex time
[*]Live invalidation tracking per pattern, with dedicated alert once one breaks
[*]Near-miss candidate marker and score-breakdown debug table for threshold tuning
[*]Dashboard with status, active pattern count, best score, bias, EPA and invalidation level
[*]Bull/bear alerts with bar-close confirmation
[/list]

